43 SECTION 7.(a) Article 9A of Chapter 90 of the General Statutes is amended by
44 adding the following new sections to read:
45 "§ 90-171.36B. Advanced practice registered nurse licensure.
46 (a) No advanced practice registered nurse shall practice as an advanced practice
47 registered nurse unless the nurse is licensed by the Board under this section.
48 (b) An applicant for a license to practice as an APRN shall apply to the Board in a format
49 prescribed by the Board and pay a fee in an amount determined under G.S. 90-171.27.
50 (c) The Board shall adopt rules, not inconsistent with this Article, which identify the
51 criteria which must be met by an applicant in order to be issued a license.
Page 6 House Bill 514-First Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "§ 90-171.36C. Advanced practice registered nurse licensure; grandfathering exceptions.
2 (a) The Board shall issue an APRN license to any person recognized by the Board as an
3 APRN or approved to practice as an APRN in this State on or before the date that this section
4 becomes law.
5 (b) An advanced practice registered nurse licensed under this section shall maintain all
6 practice privileges provided to licensed advanced practice registered nurses under this Chapter.
7 "§ 90-171.36D. Advanced practice registered nurse licensure renewal; reinstatement.
8 (a) An applicant for renewal of an APRN license issued under this Article shall apply for
9 licensure renewal according to the frequency and schedule established by the Board and pay the
10 required fee.
11 (b) Failure to renew the APRN license before the expiration date shall result in automatic
12 forfeiture of the right to practice nursing as an APRN in North Carolina until such time as the
13 license has been reinstated.
14 (c) An APRN licensee who has allowed his or her license to lapse by failure to renew
15 may apply for reinstatement in a manner prescribed by the Board and pay the required fee.
16 (d) The Board shall adopt rules, not inconsistent with this Article, which identify the
17 criteria which must be met by an applicant for APRN license renewal or reinstatement."
